Fresh off his 2020 XXL Freshman nomination, Jack Harlow pays homage to friend and NBA player Tyler Herro‚Äîwith whom he is pictured on the single‚Äôs cover‚Äîon the eponymous single ‚ÄúTyler Herro.‚Äù The song marks Harlow‚Äôs first solo release since his chart-topping remix of his breakout hit ‚ÄúWHATS POPPIN‚Äù and is the first single of his debut album Thats What They All Say.

‚ÄúTyler Herro‚Äù surfaced online ten days prior to its official release on October 22, 2020, alongside a music video starring friends Harlow and Herro.
genius_annotations:
[('Can‚Äôt touch me, I got instincts', [['This could be a reference to Dragon Ball Super‚Äôs Goku‚Äôs ‚ÄúUltra Instinct‚Äù technique, where he becomes untouchable through autonomous dodging.']]), ('Hotel room like heaven on earth', [['Heaven on earth is a massage parlor from the movie Rush Hour 2 where the two main characters, Inspector Lee (Jackie Chan) and Detective James Carter (Chris Tucker), went to relax on their vacation in China.

In this establishment, they were given the privilege of picking any of the beautiful masseuses for their spa session.

Also a phrase used to describe an experience to be as close as it gets to heaven.']]), ('Extreme like BMXing', [['BMX is a known cycle sport performed on bikes, as the acronym is an abbreviation for ‚Äúbicycle motocross‚Äù. People professionally compete in BMX racing or perform in freestyle BMX.

Harlow is probably referring to their haters and how they are ‚Äúextreme‚Äù in their negativity towards him and his success.']]), ('Locked in the house, but I‚Äôm plottin‚Äô things', [['Jack refers here to the COVID-19 pandemic that put the world on pause and many people inside. However, during this time Jack made some of his best music, including this song and his hit album Thats What They All Say.']]), ('Green room chock-full of all my comforts', [['A green room is the artist‚Äôs personal room backstage at concert venues. Usually an artist request certain things for the venue to put in their green room, like foods and drinks.

When an artist is less popular, venues are less likely to meet the artist‚Äôs request, but now that Jack is popular he can ask for whatever he wants.

It could also mean that Jack has a lot of women waiting for him backstage, in his green room.']]), ('I came home nice, but I‚Äôm goin‚Äô back mean', [['Jack lives with one foot in his hometown of Louisville, Kentucky and one foot in Atlanta with his label Generation Now. When Jack comes home to Louisville he is often seen in public socializing with his community, but when he‚Äôs in Atlanta he‚Äôs in business mode.']]), ('She at the video tryna be in this scene
 Used to fantasize ‚Äòbout bein‚Äô this seen (Seen)', [['These two lines represent entendre and false-repetition. In saying that she‚Äôs trying to be in the scene and fantasize about being seen, he‚Äôs referring to getting views which could also be implying that they‚Äôll be doing something sexual in nature. The following line could mean obtaining fame by sticking with someone exploding in popularity like him, but also using the implications that small-town women turned porn stars use similar tactics.

At the same time, he maintains the consonant repetition though he changes the last word after saying scene x3 then seen once.']]), ('I‚Äôm tryna tell y‚Äôall boys, I got a few songs I could sell y‚Äôall boys
 I tried it back then, it was, ‚ÄúHell nah, boy‚Äù (Nah)', [['This is a reference to him selling tapes of the Kentucky hip-hip group Nappy Roots song, ‚ÄúAwnaw‚Äù, when he was younger.']]), ('Made a mil‚Äô and I don‚Äôt know what to blow it on', [['Following his hit ‚ÄúWHATS POPPIN,‚Äù, Harlow has no plans for his first million dollars.

In contrast, Tyler Herro sat down with GQ Sports in March 2020 to record how he blew his first million. The video has since gone viral:

https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=La1lj4mYpc4']]), ('These boys pussy and they PMSing', [['Harlow criticizes his haters, calling them pussies and alluding to their moodiness and negative attitudes.

genius_description:
‚ÄúWhat That Speed Bout‚Äù is the first single from producer Mike WiLL Made-It‚Äôs upcoming third studio album. The song marks the anticipated first collaboration between YoungBoy Never Broke Again and Nicki Minaj and features co-production from 30 Roc.

Released two years after Youngboy‚Äôs 2018 eponymous single, ‚ÄúNicki Minaj,‚Äù ‚ÄúWhat That Speed Bout" was teased in a July 2020 Twitter post. Later, in August 2020, Mike WiLL Made-It previewed the song during an Instagram Livestream. Months after, Nicki Minaj announced the track‚Äôs November 2020 release via Instagram.

‚ÄúWhat That Speed Bout‚Äù was released along with a futuristic music video starring the three collaborators.

As Jung Kook explained, ‚ÄúStay‚Äù was originally intended to be the last track on his mixtape. The lyrics were entirely in English, but changed partially to Korean as they decided to use it on the group‚Äôs album, but the original title remained unchanged.

genius_description: On ‚ÄúSomebody‚Äôs Problem,‚Äù Morgan Wallen talks about meeting a girl at a party. He concludes that a girl as attractive as her must be alone at this party (and not with a significant other) because someone else thought of her as a problem and probably regrets breaking up with her. He is saying that he would treat her much better than anyone who was foolish enough find any issue with a girl this attractive, and whatever flaw someone else found in her would not be a problem for him at all.
genius_annotations:
[('She‚Äôs somebody‚Äôs problem, somebody‚Äôs goodbye', [['Somebody‚Äôs problem means someone that is attacking you, physically or mentally. When thinking about said person you might feel love, but it is closely followed by sadness as they can not help you, or bring you happiness.

Somebody‚Äôs goodbye is relating to the need for someone to say goodbye for the need of a new hello']]), ('A ‚ÄôBama red 4Runner pulled into the party', [['‚Äú‚ÄòBama red‚Äù is a reference to the distinct crimson color of the University of Alabama‚Äôs athletic teams, while 4Runner refers to the Toyota 4Runner.

As shown in his song ‚ÄúHad me by Halftime,‚Äù Wallen is a fan of the Tennessee Volunteers, a rival of the Alabama Crimson Tide. However, in October 2020, videos surfaced on Twitter of Wallen partying in Tuscaloosa, Alabama at the University of Alabama. Due to the fact he appeared without a mask during the coronavirus pandemic in the videos, his scheduled appearance on Saturday Night Live was postponed.

Wallen eventually appeared as the musical guest on Saturday Night Live on December 5, 2020 even appearing in a sketch poking fun at his Alabama party incident.']]), ('Somebody‚Äôs last call number that they can‚Äôt find', [['Wallen is saying that whoever dated this girl in the past did not put the effort that she deserved into the relationship. The fact that she was this person‚Äôs last call could mean that they thought of her only when they needed something, but they did not truly care about her, since this person lost her phone number.']]), ('Somebody‚Äôs reason for leavin‚Äô on the porch light', [['‚ÄúTo leave on the porch light‚Äù is a popular metaphor for hoping that someone who is missing will return. In this case, Wallen is saying whoever may have broken up with this girl in the past probably regrets it and hopes she might take them back one day.']]), ('With a 30-A sticker on the back windshield', [['‚Äú30-A‚Äù refers to Highway 30-A which runs along the Gulf Coast in the Florida Panhandle. Several beaches sit right off of Highway 30-A, and many cars in the South sport 30-A stickers to commemorate the scenic route.']])]

Look below and zoom anywhere

The use of the word ‚Äòzoom‚Äô here is interesting when considering the amount of people who started using Zoom, the video conferencing app, during the 2020 pandemic. The number of users went from 10 million in 2019 to 300 million in 2020. It‚Äôs used in 90,000 schools in 20 countries, including South Korea.

BTS have been enrolled at the Global Cyber University: RM, Suga and J-Hope are majored in, and Jimin, V and Jungkook are majoring in Entertainment & Media.

These lines may reference how people can now travel to school, work, etc. from their rooms thanks to video conferences replacing real life interaction. In fact, BTS have even attended talk shows via Zoom.']]), ('ÏÉùÍ∞ÅÏùÄ ÏÉùÍ∞ÅÏù¥ Î∞îÍæ∏Î©¥ Îèº

In an interview with Weverse magazine, j-hope explained the significance of his verse and the importance of perspective in helping him get through the difficulties during the pandemic:

It all depends on how you look at it. Say there‚Äôs some kind of food. You might feel lonely while eating it by yourself, but if you forget about your loneliness for a minute and think, ‚ÄòThere is no difference in food I would be eating out (with other people) anyway,‚Äô then it‚Äôs just like eating out. So even though I was stuck feeling lonely at home, I started to think of it as another trip instead. I thought of my room as my world, and delivery food as a three-star hotel meal. As you can tell from the title, I worked on that song by thinking about the way I endured this year so far. [I‚Äôve decided to change the way I think] because I get a lot of love. Because I‚Äôm in this position and in this place, there‚Äôs things I have to deal with, and I should do things and think things I am able to bear. On ‚ÄúShots Fired,‚Äù the introduction to Megan‚Äôs debut album, she promptly and briefly addresses the July 2020 shooting incident that involved her and Tory Lanez‚Äìwhom she refrains from naming on the song.

The song serves to end the conversation around the shooting so that the rest of the album is focused on what else Megan has to say. She also briefly calls into question the lack of justice for Breonna Taylor and other black women.

The track notably samples ‚ÄúI‚Äôm Afraid the Masquerade Is Over‚Äù by David Porter, which is the source used in The Notorious B.I.G.‚Äôs hit, ‚ÄúWho Shot Ya?‚Äù

genius_description:
‚ÄúPain Away‚Äù is the second track on Meek Mill‚Äôs November 2020 surprise Quarantine Pack EP.

On ‚ÄúPain Away,‚Äù Meek Mill talks about how he hopes his success and the money that comes with it might help to ease his pain caused by the violence and injustice he has seen in the world.  Despite the fact that his career has taken care of him and his family financially, he still feels obligated to use his money and his platform to help make the world a safer place.
genius_annotations:
[('Washin‚Äô blood with bleach don‚Äôt wash the stain away', [['Bleach is a cleaning agent often used to clean and contaminate DNA evidence. The stain here  is not a literal stain. Lil Dirk is conveying that no matter how much you try and get rid of the evidence, the effect of your actions stays with you as part of you and haunts you as a stain on your memory.']]), ('Hangin‚Äô with the real, won‚Äôt hang with lames today (Lames today)', [['What Lil Durk is trying to say is that he only hanging with the reals & no lame goofies namsaying. To elaborate , Lil Durk references individualas whom he would consider a blessed presence nanmean. He aint neva gonna hang with no lames or goofs even if that means taking a ‚ÄúL‚Äù. To sum it up, only real ni**as in the cut']]), ('It‚Äôs more than us to see our sons and all our daughters eat
 ‚ÄôCause I got cops tryna lock me, opps out tryna slaughter me', [['Here, Meek Mill is saying it‚Äôs not enough for him to simply provide financially for his family; he wants to make the world a safer place for his children to grow up in.

Meek Mill has recently been working on prison reform with rapper Jay-Z through an organization the two co-founded called REFORM Alliance. On September 30, 2020, California Governor Gavin Newsom signed a bill into law that will limit probation sentences in California. REFORM Alliance had been working to support this bill and saw the signing as a success.']]), ('I feel like a Crip ‚Äôcause I can‚Äôt even trust my blood (Blood)', [['The Crips and Bloods are two rival gangs in America. Communities such as Englewood, Riverdale, and most famously O Block contribute to Chicago being one of the most dangerous cities in the USA.

Despite the all the violence and killings in Chicago, Durkio consistently praises Chicago and has been working to reduce gun violence in his city. This same gun violence has unfortunately lead to Durk loosing many of his friends. Rapper LA Capone, manager OTF Chino Dolla, cousin OTF Nunu (Nuski), and most recently rapper King Von are just some of the many friends Durkio has lost.']])]

genius_description:
‚ÄúShow Out‚Äù is a track of triumph and vigor, which combines related genres of drill and hip hop.  Cudi flows in a never-before seen trio alongside the posthumous Brooklyn rapper Pop Smoke and London rapper Skepta. Produced by Cudi‚Äôs OG team of Dot Da Genius and Plain Pat (as well as Heavy Mellow and Gravez), Cudi returns to his roots both vocally and instrumentally.

Although Cudi is not known for a history of gang violence or drug dealing, he relates to the sentiments of Skepta and the late Pop Smoke through their dedication to their team and their cause.  The chorus depicts war-like behavior, pinning the rappers' teams against any enemies.
The verses continue this fighting theme through several mentions to the rappers' deep teams who stand by their respective leaders.
genius_annotations:
[('What‚Äôs it cost? Everything', [['Pretty sure this is an Infinity War reference.']]), ('Clip in the stick, stick in the coat (Boom)', [['‚ÄúClip in the stick‚Äù is slang for ‚Äúammo in the firearm‚Äù, meaning that the gun is loaded with ammunition.



Stick in the coat means that the ‚Äústick‚Äù aka a rifle is inside the coat. This continues the Russian nesting doll/inception theme of this particular line.']]), ('Roll the Fronto', [['Fronto is a raw tobacco leaf used to roll marijuana. It is Brooklyn drill‚Äôs favorite blunt wrap.

It had been referenced frequently in the drill rap sense. Probably most notably was Rowdy Rebel on ‚ÄúComputers‚Äù, his 2014 collab with Bobby Shmurda where he said:

Smoking Fronto, bitch no Phillies']]), ('And they got guns same size as Kevin Hart
 Please don‚Äôt think it‚Äôs a joke', [['American comedian, Kevin Hart, is 1.63 m (5'4") and often makes jokes about himself being short and small.

Despite Kevin Hart being known for being short for a human, a gun the size of Kevin Hart is actually very large.  Skepta means to convey that his crew has big guns and is not to be messed with.']]), ('Man down, roll up
 Man down, roll up', [['This is a slight interpolation of a line in Pop Smoke‚Äôs collaborative 2019 track ‚ÄúGATTI‚Äù with the JACKBOYS and Travis Scott. In the first verse, he raps:

Man down (Woo), all you see is helicopters (Grr)

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kx7P_ENnDPE']]), ('Got the ladies hittin‚Äô my phone (Brr)
 Got the mandem hittin‚Äô the woah (Greaze)
 Me plus ten on the list, they know how I‚Äôm comin‚Äô, I‚Äôm bringin‚Äô the bros', [['Skepta is describing the activities of his close crew, the girls yearning to be around him and the guys he brings to all his events. Mandem is UK slang for a group of men or crew who are, hitting the woah, a dance move that became widely popular in 2018.



This line is also a reference to Skepta‚Äôs 2016 track ‚ÄúLadies Hit Squad‚Äù which is an ode to romancing fine ladies.']]), ('Dream on, fly away (Yeah), dream on (Uh)', [['Dream On is the name of Cudi‚Äôs now-dissolved  record label.  The label was originally founded in 2009 with long-time friends and producers Plain Pat and Emile Haynie, but was short-lived as it dissolved in February 2011.

Despite the label fading away, Cudi has never stopped dreaming on.']]), ('Left wrist Audemars Piguet, right wrist whippin‚Äô the whip on the stove
 He don‚Äôt care ‚Äôbout fame, he just tryna get rich on the low', [["‚ÄúWhippin' the whip on the stove‚Äù is related to a common phrase which refers to the process of cooking crack. The process roughly consists of adding ice to a mixture of boiled cocaine and baking soda, then vigorously whipping to quickly cool it until it coagulates into crack.  This method of cutting cocaine has been used for decades as a way to get rich quickly.



This line mirrors a lyric from Pusha T‚Äôs track ‚ÄúDrug Dealers Anonymous‚Äù, in which Jay Z raps:

Life made me ambidextrous
Countin‚Äô with my right, whippin‚Äô white with my left wrist"]]), ('Back on tour with the gang and it‚Äôs sold out
 Twenty-two dates, I ain‚Äôt missin‚Äô a show', [['Prior to the 2020 global pandemic, Skepta was busy touring.  Skepta put on shows in exactly 22 different locations across the world throughout 2019, as reported by Resident Advisor.  As he traveled from the UK to Australia, he didn‚Äôt miss a show, and based on his recent tour reviews, he certainly ‚Äúshow[ed] out‚Äù as well. Pop Smoke was also the supporting act for the four UK dates of Skepta‚Äôs 2019 ‚ÄòIgnorance Is Bliss‚Äô tour. These were Pop Smoke‚Äôs only and last performances outside of the US.']]), ('All my niggas is ready to go
 Pop Smoke, big smoke', [['This is a possible reference to the only known footage of Pop Smoke and Skepta together.

In the clip Skepta says ‚ÄúBig Pop‚Äù and Pop Smoke responds ‚ÄúYeah! Big Smoke‚Ä¶ Pop Smoke!‚Äù which acknowledges the similarity between his artist name and Skepta‚Äôs moniker ‚ÄòBig Smoke‚Äô.

Skepta may be referring to what Pop Smoke said, responding by flipping the order of the names, possibly as a sign of respect or tribute.

genius_description:
On ‚ÄúGnat,‚Äù the third promotional single from Eminem‚Äôs Music to Be Murdered By project, the veteran rapper covers such topics as the COVID-19 pandemic, his former addiction to valium, and Donald Trump‚Äôs administration.

The song‚Äôs music video was directed by Cole Bennett‚Äôs Lyrical Lemonade, who also shot the music video for the standard album‚Äôs ‚ÄúGodzilla‚Äù back in January 2020. Upon the December 2020 release of Side B and the ‚ÄúGnat‚Äù video, Cole tweeted:

new video with @eminem out now. it is a beautiful thing when you get to recreate nostalgic moments with your childhood heroes.

[('With the dope, I‚Äôm an OG, I‚Äôm like the G.O.A.T.​', [['G.O.A.T. is an anagram for greatest of all time. Eminem is arguably the greatest rapper of all time.']]), ('I will anni-nihilate, kill them
 I‚Äôll fuck around and pile eight million
 Dead little juveniles', [['This could be a very subtle reference to the Star Wars movie franchise (specifically the Skywalker saga) and the character of Anakin Skywalker.

In the movies, Anakin is often referred to as his nickname ‚Äì Ani. His eventual conversion to the dark side of the Force was cemented when he murdered a group of juveniles.

Em pauses when pronouncing annihilate, separating out anni which sounds like Ani ‚Äì couple this with talk of killing children and there is suggestion for the Star Wars link.

This wouldn‚Äôt be the first time Eminem references these films in his lyrics, either:


Rain Man, Encore
Stay Wide Awake, Relapse
Old Time‚Äôs Sake, Relapse
You‚Äôre Never Over, Recovery
Rhyme or Reason, Marshall Mathers LP2']]), ('I‚Äôve got my nose in the air like a Boeing', [['Boeing is an aerospace company that manufactures, produces and sells all stuffs related to planes and aircraft.

Em compares himself to a jet or plane which flies with its nose in the air and makes him feel like he is better than anyone else in the rap game.


A Boeing Jet in The Air']]), ('I mean my penmanship at times tends to get ill, violence but with skill', [['Eminem has numerously likened his pen or pencil to a hazardous weapon and stated that he‚Äôs prepared to use his words as a weapon against anyone.
as we hear in ‚ÄúVenom‚Äù:

Shotgun p-p-pellets in the felt pen
Cocked, fuck around and catch a hot one

or in ‚ÄúRap God‚Äù:

My pen‚Äôll go off when I half-cock it

However he‚Äôs taking advantage of his violent weapon intelligently and somewhat ‚Äúskillfully‚Äù and that‚Äôs why he‚Äôs made a secured legacy and heritage in rap and reached to these kinds of trophies and ribbons.

Furthermore, in the music video we see him writing with a knife, which supports the message that his writing is somewhat violent.



Additionally, ‚ÄúViolence but with skill‚Äù is Marshall Arts, referring again to himself since rap is ‚ÄúMarshall‚Äôs [Mathers] art‚Äù']]), ('Got her at the pole like voting with no clothing', [['Em insinuates the woman is pole dancing for him and playing-on the word ‚Äúpole‚Äù which is a homonym for ‚Äúpoll.‚Äù Interestingly, there was a massive voter turnout for the 2020 elections impacted mainly by the presidential ticket.']]), ('[Verse 1]', [['On December 21, 2020, the Spited Youtube channel posted a video highlighting the rhyming patterns on the two verses and the chorus :

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7CLcPgCpIiw&ab_channel=Spited']]), ('‚ÄòCause I‚Äôm so fuckin‚Äô dope (Dope) and you‚Äôre a fiend
 And that‚Äôs the one thing that hasn‚Äôt changed (Nope)
 For some semblance of normalcy', [['Eminem claims his fans are addicted to his music like addicts are to drugs. Moreover, he conflates ‚Äúdope‚Äù with ‚Äúyou‚Äôre a fiend,‚Äù making it sound like endorphin, which is a chemical that relieves pain and stress.



Em has likened his music to drugs before, on Kid Cudi‚Äôs July 2020 single, ‚ÄúThe Adventures of Moon Man & Slim Shady,‚Äù:

Bread is long like an Italian sub, I am drugs
That is probably why your opinion of me‚Äôs high as fuck

He also used similar lines on a 2009 ‚ÄúBET Cypher‚Äù alongside Mos Def and Black Thought:

Like a dope fiend opening up a bottle of dopamine
You‚Äôre just hoping he don‚Äôt get rope for your throat to choke anything']]), ('Like, fuck, now my name rings out like a sponge mop
 And my drip was a drop
 In the bucket, so that gun shot
 You just heard just now in that one spot', [["Eminem uses homophone wordplay between the phrases ‚Äúrings out‚Äù and ‚Äúwrings out.‚Äù ‚ÄúDrip‚Äù is a slang term similar in meaning to ‚Äúswag,‚Äù while ‚Äúa drop in the bucket‚Äù is something small and insignificant.

The water-related scheme is reminiscent of the lyrics on ‚ÄúYou Gon' Learn‚Äù from the original version of Music to Be Murdered By, released in January 2020:

I‚Äôll get to doing what a leaky faucet do
But I ain‚Äôt talkin' drip when I say that I‚Äôll get the drop on you

Gunfire can also ‚Äúring out,‚Äù so this ties into the ‚Äúhair trigger‚Äù remark in the previous line as well as the 9mm wordplay in the next line."]]), ('I‚Äôm hoping a little codeine‚Äôll get me OD‚Äôin‚Äô', [['Eminem mentions the popular drug codeine and the event that an overdose can occur.

Em‚Äôs drug use of Valium, Ambien, and Vicodin started when he was filming in 2002 while also trying to tour and be a father. This drug use, however, never got out of hand and he never endured lethal withdrawals. In 2006, after years of controlled drug use, Eminem sank into the depths of medication and codeine. The tortured rapper immersed himself in a willingly decadent rock and roll world in which a doomed artist can only live and be creative when in a chemically-induced trance.

Eminem was one of the lucky few to get out of the unhealthy, uncontrolled drug use. He is now over a decade sober and does not use prescription medication or codeine. He also advocates for drug-induced youth to get out of their addictions and sustain a sober lifestyle.

This wouldn‚Äôt be the first occasion when he would rap about overdosing on codeine. In the track ‚ÄúNo Regrets‚Äù he refers to this subject once more:

Yeah, they miss the old me
I think they want me to OD on codeine
They want my life in turmoil like in ‚Äò03']]), ('Still got that heroin lyrical drip with that morphine and that Thorazine', [["Chlorpromazine ,marketed under the brand name Thorazine among others, is an antipsychotic medication. It is primarily used to treat psychotic disorders such as schizophrenia.



Many modern psychiatrists believe that ‚Äò'Marilyn Monroe‚Äô‚Äò was diagnosed with and suffered from all sorts of mood disorders like Paranoid, Schizophrenia and Borderline Personality Disorder symptoms of which include identity issues, addictive behavior, and suicidal behavior.

Marilyn‚Äôs death was caused by an overdose of sedative drugs that was used to treat her mood disorders. Opiates are narcotic sedatives, hence the mention of heroin and morphine.

The word ‚Äúheroin‚Äù  also could be interpreted as the word ‚Äúheroine‚Äù describing Marilyn even further as she was a feminist icon, ergo a heroine to many.

Also the play on the words ‚ÄúMonroe‚Äù and ‚ÄúHeroin‚Äù is noticeable. Monroe is the largest city and county seat of Monroe County in the U.S. state of Michigan. Monroe is located approximately 14 miles (23 km) north of Toledo, Ohio and 25 miles (40 km) south of Detroit. it is a town which he visited years back. It‚Äôs very distinguished for Heroin distribution on the grounds that it‚Äôs in the middle of Toledo and Detroit.



Monroe‚Äôs historic downtown on M-125"]])]
